 4. Validate the amount of open ports before allowing the user to rent the machine. The system will ensure that the minimum amount of open ports on the template are available before letting the renter rent the machine and find that out for themselves later. We are also increasing our default template to have more than 2 ports based on customer feedback.

The validator will run a synthetic synthetic test on the GPU right before giving the GPU to the renter, and as long as the miner passes that second test, they will be eligible to be rented. Otherwise, we will remove that GPU from our site.
